timeline.bodyText:
The problem with this is that it's unclear what the test wants the title to be. For "unit" tests like this you want you test to be as in charge of the dependencies as possible. Given the ViewModel is a mock you can set the value that will be returned from getFormName like so:
when(formSaveViewModel.getFormName()).thenReturn("blah");

This means you could write a test for both the null and non null case. Here I I'd imagine you're only testin the null case as the mock will return null from getFormName().

